  "body": "**What keywords did you search in Kubernetes issues before filing this one?**: terminationGracePeriodSeconds, termination, network.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**: Bug report\r\n\r\n**Kubernetes version**: 1.6.0\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- **Cloud provider or hardware configuration**: GCP and minikube\r\n- **OS**: `Alpine Linux v3.4`\r\n- **Kernel**: Linux 4.7.2\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\nPod in \"Terminating\" state loses network connection two minutes after it was scheduled for termination, while still performing the work in the container. The bug prevents a pod from gracefully finishing the work.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\nTerminating pod should gracefully finish the work with network being available according to `terminationGracePeriodSeconds`.\r\n\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it** (as minimally and precisely as possible):\r\n\r\nRun a pod that does something like:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\nrequire 'net/http'\r\nloop do\r\n  Net::HTTP.get_response('google.com', '/')\r\n  sleep 1\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\nFor convenience I pushed the script to the docker hub (`kirshatrov/sleep-with-signals:v2`).\r\n\r\nCreate the pod with longer terminationGracePeriodSeconds policy:\r\n\r\n```\r\napiVersion: v1\r\nkind: Pod\r\nmetadata:\r\n  name: gracefully-terminating-pod\r\nspec:\r\n  containers:\r\n  - name: app\r\n    image: kirshatrov/sleep-with-signals:v2\r\n  terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 1500\r\n```\r\n\r\nDelete the pod (`kubectl delete pod gracefully-terminating-pod`) and watch the logs.\r\n\r\nAfter two minutes the network will go down and the app will crash with:\r\n\r\n```\r\nFailed to open TCP connection to google.com:80 (getaddrinfo: Try again) (SocketError)\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know**:\r\n\r\nThis happens both in GCP and Minikube on Kubernetes 1.6.0.\r\nThe kind of work we're performing in the containers is not safely interruptible and we'd like to use longer termination timeout (`terminationGracePeriodSeconds`) to allow the pod to finish the work before it's killed. This networking issue prevents us from relying on `terminationGracePeriodSeconds`.\r\n\r\ncc @ibawt @Sirupsen @dwradcliffe @dturn",
